org.linqs.psl.config

Class Option

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.linqs.psl.config.Option

  • public class Option
extends Object
    A container for configuration options. This is the preferred way to interface with configuration options compiled into the code. Calls to the get methods will in-turn call into the Config option with the correct name and default value. If flags are set (such as FLAG_POSITIVE), they will be checked when a value is retrieved (via a get method).

      • set

        public void set(Object value)
        Set the value (in the Config) for this Option. This will overwrite any previously set value. No type checking is done on the passed-in value.

      • get

        public Object get()
        Fetch the Option's configuration value from the Config class. This is the most general get method, one with a specific type should generally be used. This is the only provided get method that does not use a default.
